<div class="faqs">
  <div class="container pt-5 mt-5">
    <h1 class="text-center font-weight-bold text-label mb-5">FAQS</h1>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-12">
        <div class="mb-4">
          <h5 class="text-center bg-green text-white py-3">What is HomeSchool?</h5>
          <p class="text-muted bg-light py-3 px-5">
            HomeSchool brings the best parts of education to your home with 
            willing teachers, small class sizes, and a personalized curriculum.
            Children in the same neighbourhood and classes can study together for 
            3 - 4 hours a day. Your children receive an enriching experience with 
            greater flexibility and more personalized attention than the traditional 
            schools can offer - all in a safe and inspiring home learning environment. 
            HomeSchool does not intend to replace the existing education framework it is 
            only expected to run until schools are fully open to all classes. 
            We just want our children to study, even in COVID!
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-6">
        <div class="mb-4">
          <h5 class="px-5 bg-green text-white py-3 d-flex justify-content-between" data-toggle="collapse" aria-expanded="false" data-target="#collapseExample" aria-controls="collapseExample" style="cursor: pointer;">
          <span>Why do we need a teacher?</span>
          <i class="fas fa-plus text-green"></i>
          </h5>
          <p class="text-muted bg-light py-3 px-5 collapse" id="collapseExample">
            Think back to the best education experiences you've had, chances are 
            you're thinking of a teacher. Research supports that teachers have the 
            largest impact on student satisfaction and educational outcomes. 
            HomeSchool enables children to be allocated a teacher to guide them.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-6">
        <div class="mb-4">
          <h5 class="px-5 bg-green text-white py-3 d-flex justify-content-between" data-toggle="collapse" aria-expanded="false" data-target="#collapseExample2" aria-controls="collapseExample2" style="cursor: pointer;">
          <span>Health and Safety</span>
          <i class="fas fa-plus text-green"></i>
          </h5>
          <p class="text-muted bg-light py-3 px-5 collapse" id="collapseExample2">
            Safety is our highest priority, for your family, the children we work with, and the teacher. 
            We ask all teachers to follow all local guidelines as it relates to COVID-19. 
            Beyond that, each study-group creates its own health agreement prior to starting, 
            which we have all families, and teachers sign-off on.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-6">
        <div class="mb-4">
          <h5 class="px-5 bg-green text-white py-3 d-flex justify-content-between" data-toggle="collapse" aria-expanded="false" data-target="#collapseExample3" aria-controls="collapseExample3" style="cursor: pointer;">
          <span>Who are the teachers?</span>
          <i class="fas fa-plus text-green"></i>
          </h5>
          <p class="text-muted bg-light py-3 px-5 collapse" id="collapseExample3">
            The teachers we register go through a rigorous screen process.
            Our teachers have minimum teaching experience and often have 
            advanced diplomas and degrees with adequate recommendations.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-6">
        <div class="mb-4">
          <h5 class="px-5 bg-green text-white py-3 d-flex justify-content-between" data-toggle="collapse" aria-expanded="false" data-target="#collapseExample4" aria-controls="collapseExample4" style="cursor: pointer;">
          <span>Where does the learning happen?</span>
          <i class="fas fa-plus text-green"></i>
          </h5>
          <p class="text-muted bg-light py-3 px-5 collapse" id="collapseExample4">
            Learning can happen anywhere as long as there is enough space for the children 
            and the teachers. Lessons can happen in playrooms, backyards, living rooms, 
            and in community spaces.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

